@startuml
title Redundant Storage Architecture - Failover System

!include ../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/structural/deployment-diagram-style.iuml

actor "Cloud Consumers" as CC

cloud "Cloud Provider" as Cloud {

  component "Storage Service\nGateway" as SSG

  package "Primary Site" as PS {
    database "Primary Cloud\nStorage Device" as Primary
    rectangle "LUNs" as LUN1
    Primary --> LUN1
  }

  package "Secondary Site\n(may be different\ngeographical region)" as SS {
    database "Secondary Cloud\nStorage Device" as Secondary
    rectangle "LUNs" as LUN2
    Secondary --> LUN2
  }

  Primary <..> Secondary : storage replication\n(synchronous or asynchronous)
}

CC --> SSG : requests
SSG --> Primary : normal operation
SSG ..> Secondary : redirect on\nprimary failure

note bottom of SS
  Locating secondary device in a different
  geographical region can introduce legal
  concerns; some replication transport
  protocols also have distance restrictions.
end note

note right of SSG
  Storage service gateway is the external
  interface to cloud storage services and
  automatically redirects requests when
  the data location changes.
end note

@enduml
